  "lyrics": "[Music] Next time you see me a bit different I may be surprised with the smile A bit more effort visit In clips with a big moon still Next time I swear I'll have that money Each bill will be crispy Freshly printed in Turin County And we'll solve that I own You will be destroyed as a scale I can tell You think you know me well ► ► Next time you live, a long talk About pollinating you soon in your bones By the time we return from alone You'll be low still though Next time I'll bring you sources And a finally each one The next time you see a poor person You bleed. Sure you must lose skin. I know I will ► ► ►",
  "lyricsSegments": [
